Police followed tracks in the snow and found three bodies outside a disused cottage. All three had been killed by machine gun fire. Following forensic and other tests Army Corporal Andrew Walker was arrested and charged. He was tried at Edinburgh High Court in May, found guilty of the three murders and sentenced to 30 years imprisonment. The money, around Â£20,000 was never recovered.
